<seg id="14">The supreme audit office, Czech republic (hereinafter the "NKU, the CZECH republic") and the Najvyšší kontrolný úrad Slovenskej republiky (hereinafter referred to as "SAO SR") entered into on 12. 9. 2005 contract for cooperation in control activities.</seg>
<seg id="15">The subject of the contract was the cooperation when conducted parallel control actions of the "Administration of value added tax", included in the audit plan of the SAO, the CZECH republic for the year 2005 under no. 05/19 and "Control procedure of tax orgánov pri administration, control and vymáhaní dan z pridanej values and plnenia task within the system VIES to exchanging informácií between the member countries of the EU", included in the audit plan of the SAO SR under no. 22/2005.</seg>
<seg id="16">In parallel, the control actions carried out were of the nature of coordinated control.</seg>
<seg id="17">The result of the joint coordinated control was processed within the meaning of the European Enforcement Regulation No 31 for INTOSAI control standards.</seg>
<seg id="18">Cooperation consisted in the exchange of information to the extent provided for in the concluded treaty and in the preparation of a joint final report on the outcome of parallel checks.</seg>
<seg id="19">The purpose of the coordinated audit was the verification of selected cases of the supply and acquisition of goods at suspicious commercial transactions between the payer of value added tax from the Czech republic (hereinafter "CR") and the Slovak republic (hereinafter "SR").</seg>
<seg id="20">Both the parties contractually committed themselves to mutually provide information from public sources, from the electronic system VIES (Value Added Tax Information Exchange System) and the data about the received and sent requests for verification of business transactions between the CZECH republic and SLOVAKIA.</seg>
<seg id="21">Checks were carried out in parallel between June and December 2005.</seg>
<seg id="22">On the territory of the CZECH republic the audit was carried out by the department of the state budget and territorial departments of central Bohemia, north-west Bohemia, south Bohemia, south Moravia, central Moravia and north Moravia.</seg>
