<seg id="25">Objective of controls:</seg>
<seg id="26">The aim of parallel monitoring of the actions was to review the procedure of the financial or tax authorities in the administration of value added tax (hereinafter "VAT") after the integration of the CZECH republic and SLOVAKIA into a single internal market of the European union (hereinafter "EU") and explore the use of the electronic information system of VIES, in particular in monitoring the application of the entitlement to exemption from VAT.</seg>
<seg id="27">The controlled period of coordinated control was from 1. 5. 2004 to 30. 6. 2005.</seg>
<seg id="28">A summary of the results and evaluation of parallel control actions In the member states, the EU has introduced an electronic system VIES, which allows the tax authorities to check whether the supplier was entitled to exempt the chargeable event of VAT, and in the country of destination allows to check, whether the purchaser acquired the goods properly admitted and taxed.</seg>
