<seg id="82">VIES system</seg>
<seg id="83">In order to control the application of the right to VAT exemption in intracommunitary supplies of goods, a system of exchange of information in the field of VAT has been established within the EU.</seg>
<seg id="84">His part is the electronic system VIES, which allows the tax authorities of the member states of the EU to check whether the supplier was entitled to exempt the chargeable event of VAT and, conversely, whether the purchaser acquired the goods properly admitted and taxed.</seg>
<seg id="85">The VIEs information system is not centralised within the EU.</seg>
<seg id="86">Each member state shall develop its own vies system.</seg>
<seg id="87">National systems work on a common principle and are interconnected through the common communication network (CCN).</seg>
<seg id="88">In the CZECH republic was the VIES system interfaced with the automated tax information system (hereinafter referred to as "ADIS"), in the SR with the application software of the tax information system (hereinafter referred to as "APV DIS").</seg>
