<seg id="11">The determination of specific principles to help the refugees brought the adoption of the Geneva agreement of 1951 and new york protocol of 1967 relating to the status of refugees, whose acceptance of the governments of the signatory countries committed themselves to apply them in their foreign-policy orientation.</seg>
