<seg id="834">BRH found that the Czech company (eCR) did not report in his tax returns for VAT in GERMANY no intracommunity acquisition hasn't even HKE the German DUTY.</seg>
<seg id="835">So it is possible that the Czech company has declared all intracommunitary deliveries uniformly as intracommunitary deliveries from the Czech Republic.</seg>
<seg id="836">The Sao found that (eCR) reported no intracommunitary delivery to Austria but intracommunitary delivery to Denmark.</seg>
<seg id="837">Examination of the taxation of intrakomunitárního acquisition in Austria would require the cooperation of at least four tax administrations (the austrian, the Czech, Danish and German), although this case does not show any sign of tax fraud or evasion.</seg>
<seg id="838">Further, the SAO and BRH examine the transactions in order to highlight the differences between declaring in a tax return and data from the VIES, which were caused by the different legal treatment of VAT in 2004.</seg>
<seg id="839">Controlled cases also demonstrate that changes in the legislation need time to apply the new legislation into practice by both payers and tax authorities:</seg>
<seg id="840">22. In SH for II. until IV. quarter 2004 the Czech payer reported an intracommunitary delivery to the German payer totalling CZK 792 977 452 (EUR 25 197 885).</seg>
<seg id="841">Over the same period, another Czech payer reported an intracommunity delivery to another German payer totalling CZK 18,157,265 (EUR 576,970).</seg>
