<seg id="522">Checks on VAT for large companies is governed by the same rules as the tax control in general, i.e. the relevant provisions are enshrined in the following legislation: • the German fiscal code (AO), • the law on fiscal administration (FVG), • regulations on tax inspections (BpO).</seg>
<seg id="523">Other methodological documents are also in force.</seg>
<seg id="524">German fiscal code</seg>
<seg id="525">Statutory provisions relating to control are enshrined in articles 193-203 of the German fiscal code in section IV - Tax inspection on the spot. These articles in particular provide the rules of admissibility of tax inspection on the spot (i.e. in the premises of the enterprise), their range around the page of the course, the rules for the division of responsibilities, the form and content of the notice of inspection, control principles, the obligations of the entity to cooperate and the prerequisites for the implementation of the final discussion and communication of the inspection report.</seg>
<seg id="526">On-the-spot tax inspections are carried out by the responsible tax authorities (article 195 of the code).</seg>
<seg id="527">The Fiscal Governance Act referred to in Article 5.1 (1), in connection with Article 5.1 (1), 19 of the act, participation in on-the-spot tax inspections carried out by the federal Central Tax Office is compulsory.</seg>
<seg id="528">The authorities involved shall agree together on the spot the nature and extent of the federal Central Tax Office's participation in tax controls.</seg>
<seg id="529">In addition, it has the Federal central tax office the right to require specific businesses, which selects, were subjected to scrutiny at a time you designate.</seg>
<seg id="530">In this case, it can declare the rules for the implementation and content of the inspection at the premises of these companies.</seg>
<seg id="531">The regulations on tax inspections According to the article 108.7 of the German constitution were regulations on tax inspections (German acronym BpO 2000) agreed by the Federal council (Bundesrat, upper house of the German parliament, in which are represented the governments of the länder).</seg>
<seg id="532">These administrative regulations apply for the on-site inspection by the financial authorities of the länder and the Federal central tax office.</seg>
<seg id="533">Undertakings shall be classified according to size at regular intervals in accordance with Article 3 of BPO 2000.</seg>
<seg id="534">Large enterprises are subject to subsequent control (article 4.2 BpO).</seg>
